  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "Yes, you can make a voice call from your iPad using a Jio SIM, but there are certain conditions and steps you need to follow:\n\n1. **iPad Model**: Ensure your iPad has cellular capabilities, as Wi-Fi-only models do not have a SIM slot and cannot make calls through a cellular network.\n\n2. **Jio SIM**: Insert an active Jio SIM into your iPad's SIM slot.\n\n3. **VoLTE Support**: Your iPad must support Voice over LTE (VoLTE) as Jio relies on VoLTE for voice calls. However, iPads typically do not natively support traditional SMS or voice calls over cellular networks like iPhones do.\n\n4. **JioCall App**: You can use the JioCall app (formerly Jio4GVoice) to make voice and video calls. This app routes calls over the VoLTE network using your Jio SIM. You need to download and set up the app on your iPad.\n\n5. **Wi-Fi Calling**: If your iPad is linked to an iPhone through the same Apple ID, you can use Wi-Fi calling to make and receive calls on your iPad when both devices are connected to the internet.\n\nRemember, you will need an active internet connection via Wi-Fi or cellular data to use apps like JioCall for making calls.",
